verbose_text: The impairment of cell growth during nutrient limitation was revealed by large decreases in transcript levels for genes encoding ribosomal protein subunits and for genes coding for major metabolic functions (i.e., reductant and energy production by PSII, PSI, and the light harvesting complexes; ATP synthesis by the ATP synthase; and CO 2 fixation; Figure XREF_FIG).
evidence: ATP synthesis by the ATP synthase
